<subSubSection id="52956573CC17C133FF7EF889FE39F813" pageId="21" pageNumber="48" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="1A3036F8CC17C133FF7EF889FE39F813" blockId="21.[151,1437,1812,2032]" pageId="21" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC17C133FF7EF889FECFF89F" bold="true" box="[197,327,1890,1916]" pageId="21" pageNumber="48">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Wingspan 
<quantity id="DD779B1DCC17C133FE6BF889FDDDF89F" box="[464,597,1890,1916]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.35" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="21" pageNumber="48" unit="mm" value="23.5" valueMax="26.0" valueMin="21.0">21–26 mm</quantity>
, larger than 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC17C133FD50F888FC3FF89F" box="[747,951,1891,1916]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="rivulosa" variety="rivulosa">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC17C133FD50F888FC3FF89F" box="[747,951,1891,1916]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="48">rivulosa rivulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Wings almost transparent, with ground colour straw yellow, lighter than yellow of 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC17C133FD00F862FC1AF841" box="[699,914,1929,1954]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="rivulosa" variety="rivulosa">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC17C133FD00F862FC1AF841" box="[699,914,1929,1954]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="48">rivulosa rivulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Wing underside with faint pattern. Male genitalia similar to nominotypical subspecies, apart from the ala valvae distal end that becomes thin more gradually and is shorter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="52956573CC14C130FF7EFF7CFA03FEC5" pageId="22" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="1A3036F8CC14C130FF7EFF7CFA03FEC5" blockId="22.[151,1436,151,294]" pageId="22" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC14C130FF7EFF7CFEB7FF52" bold="true" box="[197,319,151,177]" pageId="22" pageNumber="49">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC14C130FEF3FF73FD1BFF52" box="[328,659,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rivulosa" subSpecies="ethiopica">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC14C130FEF3FF73FD1BFF52" box="[328,659,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="49">Afrasura rivulosa ethiopica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an interesting example of convergent evolution with 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC14C130FA89FF73FEFEFF3B" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="indecisa" subSpecies="orientalis">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC14C130FA89FF73FEFEFF3B" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="49">Afrasura indecisa orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Some distinguishing characters include: forewing submarginal series consisting of 
<number id="AC4724DFCC14C130FAD4FF55FA14FF3B" box="[1391,1436,190,216]" pageId="22" pageNumber="49" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7–8</number>
similarly sized dots (in 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC14C130FE0AFF0EFDBDFF1D" box="[433,565,229,254]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indecisa">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC14C130FE0AFF0EFDBDFF1D" box="[433,565,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="49">A. indecisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the 
<number id="AC4724DFCC14C130FDD1FF0EFDF1FF1C" box="[618,633,229,255]" pageId="22" pageNumber="49" value="4.0">4</number>
anterior dots are larger than the other 
<number id="AC4724DFCC14C130FBFDFF0EFBDFFF1C" box="[1094,1111,229,255]" pageId="22" pageNumber="49" value="3.0">3</number>
, which are often obsolete); marginal series of dots present (lacking in 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC14C130FD32FEE7FC83FEC6" box="[649,779,268,293]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indecisa">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC14C130FD32FEE7FC83FEC6" box="[649,779,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="49">A. indecisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); male with ciliated antennae (serratae in 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC14C130FB4CFEE7FAF1FEC6" box="[1271,1401,268,293]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indecisa">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC14C130FB4CFEE7FAF1FEC6" box="[1271,1401,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="49">A. indecisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
